{"author":{"id":"729f4229091d502775e0e5c4bfc138609955b348584d955f4229a3d76892d2a9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1470816036,"nonce":"tlPBhHCIuqFTOfSdoCQpoeHi9h0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNzAzNTUyMjE=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/906","origin":"github"},"title":"Some packages depending on package_python_2_7_numpy_1_9 currently fail to install","message":"It looks like a new revision of package_python_2_7_numpy_1_9 was posted to the toolshed in June (presumably due to an update of the atlas package). While that's all well and good, the previous revision is no longer available in the toolshed. There are a number of packages in the toolshed (e.g., package_python_2_7_deeptools_2_2_3, from the IUC) that depend on package_python_2_7_numpy_1_9. It looks like `planemo upload` or something else modifies the `tool_dependency.xml` file to set an explicit revision for dependencies when things are uploaded to the toolshed. Because of that, many packages uploaded before June 23 that depend on the numpy package will have a hard-coded revision that isn't available. The simplest solution would be to just make the previous revision (57b37f63cb84) or package_python_2_7_numpy_1_9 installable via the toolshed again.\n\nI guess this will become a non-issue once everyone switches to using conda as a dependency resolver, but in the interim...","files":null}]}